{
  "id": "019d3c5d-4d28-7033-acb0-ac8651863373",
  "content": "# Embedding Storage: Redb VECTORS Table -- Design Decision (2026-03-30)\n## What: Move 768-dim embeddings from JSON knowledge files to a dedicated Redb VECTORS table\n## Why: JSON embeddings are 92% of file size (232 MB for 14.7K entries), create useless git diffs, and slow rebuild (30-60s). Redb provides ACID/MVCC/crash-safety with ~30 lines vs ~500-1000 for a custom binary sidecar.\n## Key decisions:\n1. Table design: `TableDefinition<&[u8; 16], &[u8]>` -- UUID bytes as key, raw f32 as value via bytemuck\n2. JSON field: `#[serde(skip_serializing)]` + `#[serde(default)]` for backward compat\n3. Write path: VECTORS insert inside existing `index_entry_into` write transaction\n4. Rebuild: read VECTORS table for embeddings when JSON lacks them, fall back to JSON for pre-migration entries\n5. Migration: two-phase idempotent `migrate-vectors` command (populate VECTORS, then re-write JSON)\n6. Cold scan: `scan_cold_entries` reads from VECTORS table instead of entry.embedding\n## Alternatives rejected: Custom binary sidecar -- 7 blocking issues found (no concurrency, no crash safety, fragile tombstones, non-atomic compaction, fresh clone broken)",
